Study Purpose:
To what extent people will be okay with some kind of hypocrisy when they support a candidate. 

I don't know if this skews the data much at all, but I follow politics too closely to really give a heck as to whether or not someone has a PAC or SuperPAC -- I get that it's unfashionable, but I am less likely to support a candidate who **does not** have any sort of institutional backing, so this is something I am personally favorable towards candidates lying about.  Better to sucker the idealistic but misguided people who think that candidates should be broke than it is to be a broke candidate.
